React-native uses an array of transforms according to the [docs][1], the [`scaleX`][2] prop has been deprecated. You can scale transform on the x-axis by the inverse:

    style={{
      transform: [
        { scaleX: -1 }
      ]
    }}


  [1]: https://facebook.github.io/react-native/docs/transforms#transform
  [2]: https://facebook.github.io/react-native/docs/transforms#scalex

React Native transform accept array. So you have to pass value to transform as below : 

```lang-js
&lt;FontAwesome
    name={&#39;search&#39;}
    size={20}
    style={{
        transform: [
            {scaleX: &quot;-1&quot;},
        ]
    }}
/&gt;
```

