There are a few problems in your implementation

First you have a private `Webdriver` field named `driver` in your `Waiters` class and a public Webdriver field also named driver in your `BaseTest` class. Instead you should remove the driver field from your Waiters class and define it as a protected field in your BaseTest class.

In the Waiters constructor use `super(new ChromeDriver())` instead of `this.driver = driver`. This way the base instance will be properly initialized.

Since the driver field is protected it will be visible to any child instance so a Waiters instance can access it.

 The two classes should then look like the following:

    public class Waiters extends BaseTest {
    
        public Waiters() {
            super(new ChromeDriver());
        }
    
        public void waitToDisplayUsernameLabelDB() {
            WebDriverWait wait = new WebDriverWait(driver, 150);
            wait.until(ExpectedConditions.visibilityOfElementLocated(By.id(&quot;auth-user-name&quot;)));
        }
    }

And the BaseTest class:

    public class BaseTest {
        protected WebDriver driver;

        public BaseTest(Webdriver driver) {
           this.driver = driver;
        }
    
        protected WebDriver initiliazeDriver() {
            return driver = new ChromeDriver();
        }
    }

In your LoginPageDB class, instanciate the Waiters class correctly for example instead of

    private Waiters waiters = new Waiters(null);

write for example:

    private Waiters waiter = new Waiters();

You should not have that NPE anymore and your code should work correctly

If you want to use the initializeDriver method instead of a parameterized constructor, add an equivalent of a default constructor in the BaseTest class so it looks like:

     public class BaseTest {
        protected WebDriver driver;

        public BaseTest() {
        }

        protected WebDriver initiliazeDriver() {
            return driver = new ChromeDriver();
        }
    }

And in your Waiters class add a non parameterized constructor that will call the initializeDriver method of the base class:

        public class Waiters extends BaseTest {
           
           public Waiters() {
              initializeDriver();
           }
    
           public void waitToDisplayUsernameLabelDB() {
              WebDriverWait wait = new WebDriverWait(driver, 150);
              wait.until(ExpectedConditions.visibilityOfElementLocated(By.id(&quot;auth-user-name&quot;)));
           }
       }

